1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with abstractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the purview of cs.CL. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for abstractive summarization, which is a common application of AI in NLP. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed model is based on a dual-attention sequence-to-sequence framework, which is a machine learning technique commonly used in NLP. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the use of open information extraction and dependency parse technologies to extract fact descriptions from the source text, which are relevant to information retrieval. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a neural network-based approach for abstractive summarization, which falls under the purview of cs.NE.
